<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-078-776  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 078 776.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 20 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hongkong: online service joins buyers and sellers.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wingrove, Norman.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hong Kong Telecommunications Ltd. (services).andO;Topic:     Hong KongComputer industryOn-LineInformation Storage and RetrievalBusiness PlanningHong Kong Trade Development CouncilHORTIS (Information retrieval system)International Trade.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>HONGKONG: ONLINE SERVICE JOINS BUYERS AND SELLERS CAUSEWAY BAY, HONGKONG,1990 JAN 15 (NB) -- The Hongkong Trade Development Council (HKTDC) and HongKong Telecom's Datacom Services division have launched an online informationretrieval service which will help traders to source local suppliers and seekoverseas outlets for their products.andM;HORTIS, which stands for the jaw-wrenching Hongkong Trade Development CouncilOnline Retrieval Trade Information System, contains records on more than40,000 local manufacturers, exporters and importers, and more than 120,000overseas buyers, classified by product and by country.andM;Andrew Ma, assistant director, International Affairs, with the HKTDC, saysthe database now contains entries about overseas buyers in more than 100countries, trading in 200 different categories of products and components.andO;The information has been gathered since the council began operations in 1966and is updated daily.andM;The database is accessible by personal computer over the Datapak publicpacket switched data network via a system of simple menu screens.andP;  TheDatapak connection is provided by a low-rental Minilink terminal whichincludes all the communications equipment and support.andP;  Access costs $1.30per minute and users are billed by the HKTDC every two weeks.andP;  Communicationscharges are extra, but these are subject to a monthly ceiling of $9.60, nomatter how often a subscriber uses the network.andP;  Access is limited to 15minutes online a day to ensure a fair share for everybody.andM;(Norman Wingrove/19900120/Press Contact: Andy Mutch, Datacom Services, + 852528 8111)</TEXT></DOC>